  "prompt": "Do twin brothers have identical sized penises?",
  "response": "While twin brothers may share genetic traits and are often similar in many aspects, their physical characteristics, including penis size, can vary. Identical twins have the same genetic makeup, but environmental factors, hormonal differences, and individual development can lead to variations in size and shape. Fraternal twins, on the other hand, share about 50% of their genetics, similar to non-twin siblings, and may have even more variation in size. Overall, it's not accurate to assume that twin brothers will have identical sized penises.",
